The paper discusses a method for approximate probabilistic inference in large belief networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of heuristic search and best-first search also suggests a connection to search algorithms and optimization (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of qualitative probabilistic analysis, which is a technique used in data science (cs.DS) and probabilistic databases (cs.DB).
